    • Method Detail

      • getPartners

        public List<RegistryPartner> getPartners(String apiKey,
                                         String url)
        Request for the list of partners that this instance has, from other partners. If this instance is not in web of registries, an empty list is returned
        Parameters:
        apiKey - authentication token that this instance previously provided to instance at url
        url - location of ICE instance (partner) making request
        Returns:
        list of registry partners that this instance has, an empty list if this ICE instance is not in web of registries
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the partner with specified url could not be located
        PermissionException - if the api key could not be verified

      • getPartners

        public List<RegistryPartner> getPartners()
        Retrieves list of partners for this instance
        Returns:
        list of partners available for this ICE instance or an empty list if this instance is not in web of registries

      • addNewPartner

        public RegistryPartner addNewPartner(String userId,
                                     RegistryPartner partner)
        Adds the registry instance specified by the url to the list of existing partners (if not already in there) and sends a request to the remote instance that includes a security token that the remote instance can use to communicate with this instance.

        Information about the remote instance is still saved even when it cannot be communicated with. This allows a future communication attempt.

        Parameters:
        userId - id of user performing action (must have admin privileges)
        partner - registry partner object that contains unique uniform resource identifier & name for the registry
        Returns:
        add partner ofr

      • handleRemoteAddRequest

        protected RegistryPartner handleRemoteAddRequest(RegistryPartner request)
        Handles requests from remote ice instances that will like to be in a WoR config with this instance Serves the dual purpose of:
        • please add me as a partner to your list with token
        • add accepted; use this as the authorization token

        Note that the request is rejected if this ICE instance has not opted to be a member of web of registries

        Parameters:
        request - partner request object containing all information needed with a validated url
        Returns:
        information about this instance to be sent to the remote
